# Rasm Quality Operator

Read `.claude/skills/coding-python/SKILL.md` before editing `tools/quality/`.

## Canonical entry

```bash
uv run python -m tools.quality <rail> <verb> [args…]
```

| [INDEX] | [RAIL]          |
| :-----: | --------------- |
|   [1]   | Static cleanup + build |
|   [2]   | Unit + mutation |
|   [3]   | Rhino bridge    |

[COMMAND]
- [1] `quality static fix` / `report` / `build` / `full` / `plan`
- [2] `quality test run` / `list` / `coverage`
- [3] `quality bridge …` / `quality api …`

Use the Python module entrypoint directly. Do not add package-manager aliases for `tools.quality`.

## Conventions

- Keep orthogonal rails separate — static cleanup/build, unit/mutation, and Rhino runtime never merge.
- `quality static fix` applies scoped whitespace, style, and analyzer fixes without build.
- `quality static report` emits non-mutating fix diagnostics and reports.
- `quality static build` runs routed restore/build/analyzers; `quality static full` forces `.slnx` parity and full-solution build proof.
- `quality static plan` prints route owners, triggers, project closure, and exact dotnet commands.
- Per-rail MSBuild cache: `.artifacts/quality/<rail>/` via `ArtifactScope`; static keeps build servers and node reuse enabled. No flock, stamp files, or global coordinators.
- Default `quality test run` (managed `Rasm` target) runs MTP unit tests only. Stryker is explicit through `--mutation changed|full` and fail-fast on the mutation lock.
- Live Rhino bridge commands, bridge verify, bridge package live steps, and package stage commit use fail-fast leases. See `tools/rhino-bridge/AGENTS.md`.

## Validation

See `CLAUDE.md` §5.2 for quality gates. Operator self-test: `uv run python -m tools.quality self-test` checks CLI dependencies, manifest paths, and RhinoWIP Yak availability.
